dct_description_sm: Shows portions of Maine, New Hampshire, Massachusetts, Rhode Island, Connecticut, Nova Scotia, and the Atlantic Ocean, centered on the Boston region.
compiled, engraved and published by United States Geological Survey.
Relief shown by contours, gradient tints and spot heights. Depths shown by gradient tints and isolines.
"Compiled, engraved, and published by United States Geological Survey. George Otis Smith, director. Washington, February, 1912."
Includes index to adjoining sheets, gradient tints scale, and notes.
Also available on the Internet through the American Geographical Society Library Digital Map Collection.
